<div class=bodytext> 
<h2>Life is Ugly</h2> <p> I hesitated to echo the IMDB's
categorization of
 <a href="http://us.imdb.com/Title?0090967"
 class=imdb title="IMDB information on Down By Law"
><i>Down By Law</i></a>
 as a comedy. Holy mackerel is this thing unfunny! I registered one
laugh before the forty-five-minute mark, and maybe three more after
that.
 <a href="http://us.imdb.com/Name?Benigni,+Roberto"
 class="imdb" title="IMDB information on Roberto Benigni"
>Roberto Benigni</a>
 is pretty funny as Bob, but he's only a significant character
after an incredibly tedious, forty-five-minute build-up. When I
laughed, it tended to be a big laugh, in case you were wondering about
the 2/5. At one point, the
 <a href="http://us.imdb.com/Name?Lurie,+John"
 class="imdb" title="IMDB information on John Lurie"
>John Lurie</a>
 character complains that his cellmate's charcoal marks are making
time slow down. That's not just true for the folks in the cell.
</p>
</div> 
